---
When the user runs 'blog-jive' for the first time, it will show basic commands and a synopsis of what they should do:

    "More information can be found using: blog-jive help"

This information should be available under 'blog-jive synopsis', hide it unless the home directory doesn't exist. (help synposis)

---
If the user edits or launches a server without first setting up jive home, then create it for them and say that we did
Provide a flag to suppress the automatic-setup behavior: --no-setup

Do not launch the server unless we can verify that appropiate assets exist (provide a force flag): blog-jive server --force

---
Tell the user how to customize their install with 'blog-jive customize' (help customize)
